Interface Summary
Space Spaces are parts of the board at specific indecies.
 

Class Summary
BlankSpace A blank space lets a token roll on their next turn and move forward.
BlankSpaceTest The test class BlankSpaceTest.
Board The board stores spaces and provides access to them to main.
BoardTest The test class BoardTest.
Die The Die has an upper limit for its range and a roll function that generates a number between one and that limit.
DieTest The test class DieTest.
FairTPot When a token lands on a fair treasure pot, it gives that token a number of pieces specified by the gameâ€™s configuration.
FairTPotTest The test class FairTPotTest.
FinishFirstPlayer A FinishFirstPlayer advances its furthest token (when it may advance) until it comes within a single die roll of the finish, at which point it moves its other tokens in a similar fashion until it rolls a number required to end the game and would have the highest score if it ended the game.
FinishFirstPlayerTest The test class FinishFirstPlayerTest.
Hold When a token lands on a hold, they may not move again until they roll the number they rolled to land on the hold.
HoldQ When a tokens lands on a hold queue, they are added to the end of a queue of tokens that landed there previously.
HoldQTest The test class HoldQTest.
HoldTest The test class HoldTest.
JStack When a token moves off of a JStack, they move to the same x and y coordinate on the z level that corresponds to their roll modulo the z dimension of the board.
JStackTest The test class JStackTest.
main Main runs a game of Chutes and Ladders and Pots
PHold When a token lands on a priority hold, they are assigned the priority equal to the number rolled to land on it.
PHoldTest The test class PHoldTest.
Player Players have a number of tokens, and given a roll, choose which to move.
RandTPot When a token lands on a random treasure pot, the token rolls the die and receives a number of pieces equal to that roll.
RandTPotTest The test class RandTPotTest.
SpaceGenerator SpaceGenerator uses a Gaussian random number to choose one of the six types of spaces.
SpaceGeneratorTest The test class SpaceGeneratorTest.
Token A Token has a space on the board and a number of pieces.
TokenTest The test class TokenTest.
